<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxy38812ac03cfb4f2ba06c302e810ef43e-1">Accessibility</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="not-answered">Braille translation service <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Disabled parking<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">Disabled WC <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Induction loop<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">Text Relay <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Signing service available<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Wheelchair access<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">Step free access <span>(not answered)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContent8092ba607264484c846dd7e0790eebca">
</div>
<p>Disabled parking is available in each of the Hospital's pay and display areas. The hospital has ramps at each entrance and lifts within the building.</p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="col clear facility">
<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxy38812ac03cfb4f2ba06c302e810ef43e-2">Accommodation</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="yes">Access to TV<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="no">Internet access<span class="hidden"> (no)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Public telephone<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">Family accommodation <span>(Don't know)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Mobile phones permitted<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Private rooms only<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Single sex accommodation only<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContentdc00aaec8dd24992ad6592b690067b97">
</div>
<p>Whilst you are in hospital we aim to give you the skilled attention and caring services necessary to make sure you are comfortable and have the quickest recovery possible. <br/><br/>All staff are committed to continually improving the patient experience in relation to the service provided.  We would welcome any feedback you may have on your experience, which would help with improvements. <br/><br/>If you have any questions about your stay or treatment the doctor/nurse involved in your care will be happy to help.</p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="col clear facility">
<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxy38812ac03cfb4f2ba06c302e810ef43e-4">Counselling and Support</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="not-answered">Bereavement support <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">Translation services <span>(not answered)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContenta8ba4d050f814e3e8b00f4b75554dd1b">
</div>
<p>The Patient Advice and Liason Service (PALS) offers free, confidential, on the spot help and advice to patients, their relatives and carers on healthcare issues.The service aims to:Help sort out problems quickly and efficientlyProvide advice, support patients, their families and carers Provide information on health related issues Listen to concerns, queries and suggestions in order to improve the services we provideIf you have any comments to make, perhaps the best time to raise them is while you are attending the hospital and where the ward staff will be more then happy to discuss things with you on an individual basis.If you would prefer to speak, in confidence, to a PALS officer, they can be contacted at Bradford Royal Infirmary on 01274 364021 or at St Luke’s Hospital on 01274 365853 from Monday to Friday, 08.30am – to 16.30pm. Alternatively, please ask any member of staff to contact them on your behalf.If you would be interested in joining any of our user/support groups please feel free to ring the PALS Office, who will give the appropriate information.There are posters advertising PALS on each ward and leaflets are available from the patient information leaflet racks.</p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="col clear facility">
<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxy38812ac03cfb4f2ba06c302e810ef43e-5">Faith services</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="not-answered">Prayer area <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">On-site chapel <span>(not answered)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContent6c531d0e79284a7493da2d450cfd928a">
</div>
<p>The chaplaincy team offers confidential support to all patients and staff - to those with a faith and those with none. There is a team of multi-faith visitors who try to visit all wards on a weekly basis. Arrangements can be made for your own religious representative to visit by contacting the chaplaincy team through the nursing staff.There is a multi-faith Place of Worship in the Horton Wing at St Luke's Hospital, a Chapel in Field House and a Prayer Room in the main hospital at Bradford Royal Infirmary. Details of services and Jumma prayers will be found on notice boards or may be obtained through the nursing staff.There are team representatives from the Christia</p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
